:R-HSA-5654700  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0008150 ;
        rdfs:comment        "The FRS family of scaffolding adaptor proteins has two members, FRS2 (also known as FRS2 alpha) and FRS3 (also known as FRS2beta or SNT-2). Activation of FGFR tyrosine kinase allows FRS proteins to become phosphorylated on tyrosine residues and then bind to the adaptor GRB2 and the tyrosine phosphatase PPTN11/SHP2. Subsequently, PPTN11 activates the RAS-MAP kinase pathway and GRB2 activates the RAS-MAP kinase , PI-3-kinase and ubiquitinations/degradation pathways by binding to SOS, GAB1 and CBL, respectively, via the SH3 domains of GRB2. FRS2 acts as a central mediator in FGF signaling mainly because it induces sustained levels of activation of ERK with ubiquitous expression.<br><br><br>" ;
        rdfs:label          "FRS-mediated FGFR2 signaling" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: Gotoh, N, 2011-08-26" , "Edited: Jupe, S, 2010-02-03" , "Reviewed: Mohammadi, M, 2007-02-06 21:44:35" , "Authored: de Bono, B, 2007-01-10 10:27:18" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-5654700" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-5654696/R-HSA-5654696> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "Entity Regulation Rule 3. The relation 'Activated FGFR2 phosphorylates FRS2' 'null' 'Activated FGFR2 phosphorylates PPTN11' was inferred because:\n reaction1 has an output that is the enabler of reaction 2." , "Imported from Reactome: https://reactome.org/content/detail/R-HSA-5654700" ;
